<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SON HELPS CATCH DRIVER OF MOTHER'S STOLEN CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who witnessed his mother's car being stolen from a Saugus mini-mart 
jumped into his own pickup truck and chased the vehicle four miles, colliding 
with it once, before it broke down just as sheriff's deputies arrived and 
arrested the suspect. 
</P>
<P>
Alejandro Ortiz, 20, of Los Angeles was being held on suspicion of auto theft 
and assault with a deadly weapon, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Lt. Tim 
Peters. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
The son, Saul Holguin of Canyon Country, had accompanied his mother, Ramona 
Holguin, to a mini-mart in the 16300 block of Sierra Highway. She left the keys 
in the ignition of her 1986 Cougar and the thief got in the car and drove off, 
Peters said. 
</P>
<P>
Saul Holguin chased him north on Sierra Highway. Holguin swerved when the thief 
tried to ram his truck, but the vehicles sideswiped each other. As sheriff's 
patrol cars joined in the chase, the stolen car stalled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
