DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MOTORCYCLIST KILLED WHEN HE HITS HYDRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Studio City man died early Saturday when his motorcycle hit a fire hydrant, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old man, whose name was not released pending notification of 
relatives, was riding east on Laurel Terrace Drive near Laurel Grove Avenue 
about 4:30 a.m. when he lost control at a curve and hit the hydrant, Los 
Angeles Police Officer Dennis Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
Smith said the man was speeding and apparently was not wearing a helmet. He 
died at the scene. 
</P>
