<P>
DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BOY STRUCK BY VAN DIES OF HIS INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-year-old Saugus boy who was struck by a van as he ran across busy Seco 
Canyon Boulevard to meet a group of friends died Sunday afternoon, sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's parents requested that his name not be released, Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Sgt. Jeff Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
The teen-ager darted across the street about 3 p.m. Friday after his friends 
shouted out his name. Sheriff's deputies said the youths, who had just been 
dismissed from school, saw the accident. "He just ran out," Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the van, Penny Giacalone of Valencia, was not cited. Deputies are 
investigating the cause of the incident. 
</P>
<P>
The teen-ager died about 1 p.m. Sunday at Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, 
deputies said. 
</P>
