<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles man was killed, his passenger was in serious condition and an 
unidentified young woman was critically injured when the woman drove the wrong 
way on Interstate 5 early Sunday and crashed into another car. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified woman was driving north in the southbound lanes of Interstate 
5, near Coronado Avenue, about 1:50 a.m., according to San Diego police. Her 
vehicle collided head-on with a car driven by Jose Medina of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Medina, 28, died at the scene. His passenger, Sandra Alvarado, 21, and the 
unidentified woman, thought to be in her 20s, were taken to UC San Diego 
Medical Center. The woman carried no identification. 
</P>
