<TEXT>
<P>
A Bee of a Sale: An auction of belongings of the late Francis Bavier, better 
known as Aunt Bee on the popular "Andy Griffith Show," stirred up a fuss at her 
Raleigh, N.C., home Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Everything offered for sale, from the actress's yellowed contracts to her 
guacamole-green Studebaker Daytona with 43,000 miles, rotting tires and a 
ceramic donkey on the dashboard were snapped up by fans. A sofa was auctioned 
for $1,400 and a Queen Anne dining table with six chairs went for $1,800. One 
fan bought Bavier's rake for $45. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
