<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rap It Up: Amateur rappers will soon get an opportunity to "get on the mike" 
and maybe appear on a rap album. 
</P>
<P>
Music Plus and Epic Records are co-sponsoring a statewide contest for unsigned 
rap musicians, and the winners will be included on a compilation cassette, 
"Music Plus Street Rap '90." Music Plus officials said the project reflected 
the company's commitment to supporting rap music with a positive message and 
fighting the stereotype that all rap music is a threat. Entrants should submit 
a cassette with their original rap song and an official entry form at any Music 
Plus store between June 21 and July 15. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
