<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV/VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mom, Apple Pie and No Commercials: KCOP-TV Channel 13 will prove its 
independence on July 4 by showing nine classic films unedited and without 
commercials. Station officials said the films represent a cross-section of 
movies that could only have been made in the United States. The 22-hour 
marathon, which will start at midnight on July 3, will include "On the 
Waterfront," "Now Voyager," "The Right Stuff," "The Alamo," "The Music Man," 
"West Side Story," "A Star is Born (with Judy Garland)," "Red River" and 
"Bonnie and Clyde." GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Garland 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
