CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TRACY; 
</P>
<P>
YOUTH IN DELINQUENT PROGRAM DROWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A youth enrolled in a VisionQuest program featuring a wagon train that traveled 
from Arizona to California has drowned while trying to escape, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
John Vincent Garrison, 18, of Stockton, drowned in the Grant Line Canal north 
of Tracy, a San Joaquin County sheriff's spokesman said. Garrison and two other 
youths were attempting to swim the canal to escape authorities when he went 
under. The spokesman said VisionQuest supervisors tracked the boys and when 
they were confronted, the boys apparently decided to swim across the 
75-yard-wide canal. The boys who survived, a 16-year-old from Imperial County, 
and a 17-year-old from Stockton, were placed in Juvenile Hall. 
</P>
