<P>
LOTTO TICKET BOUGHT IN MISSION VIEJO IS WORTH $9.67 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A ticket bought in Mission Viejo had all six winning numbers for the California 
Lottery's weekend "Lotto 6-49" game and is worth $9.67 million, lottery 
officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The winning numbers, picked Saturday night, were: 31, 24, 43, 49, 3, 16, and 
the bonus number, 13. 
</P>
<P>
Thirteen tickets had five numbers plus the bonus number, and each is worth 
$117,441. Lottery officials said those tickets were bought in Oxnard, 
Huntington Beach, San Clemente, Westminster, Santa Barbara, San Fernando, 
Sylmar, Reseda, Baker, San Leandro, Modesto, Chico and Watsonville. 
</P>
