VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
BROTHERS HIT AFTER DARTING INTO TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Oxnard brothers were hospitalized after they ran in front of a car early 
Sunday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel Avila, 21, suffered head and internal injuries and was in stable 
condition at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard, nursing supervisor 
Kathy Smith said. His brother, Jose Avila, estimated to be in his teens, was in 
serious condition with internal injuries and a fractured leg, Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
At 2 a.m. Sunday, Salvador Guerrero, 22, of Oxnard was driving south on Oxnard 
Boulevard near Commercial Avenue when the Avila brothers "darted into the 
road," said Sgt. Frederick Barry of the Oxnard Police Department. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
