in which he was riding crashed. He was strapped in a booster seat secured to 
the rear seat by a seat belt. The back seat collapsed and the boy was thrown 35 
feet. A coroner's jury ruled that the seat was "flimsy and poorly constructed 
and is unsafe for public use." 
