<P>
TICKET SOLD IN CITY WORTH $9.6 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A ticket buyer in Mission Viejo won the $9.6-million jackpot in Saturday 
night's Lotto 6/49 game, it was announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The winning numbers were 3, 16, 24, 31, 43 and 49, with the bonus number 13. 
Ticket sales were $14.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
There were 13 winners in the 5-of-6 plus the bonus category. They bought their 
tickets in San Leandro, Watsonville, Chico, Modesto, Sylmar, Baker, San 
Fernando, Santa Barbara, Reseda, Westminster, San Clemente, Huntington Beach 
and Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
The estimated prize pool for Wednesday's game is $4 million. 
