<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
TESTS RUN TO FIND OUT WHAT AILS HOSPITALIZED MICHAEL JACKSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Doctors today ran a battery of tests to find out what ails pop star Michael 
Jackson who was hospitalized late Sunday with chest pains after several days of 
illness. 
</P>
<P>
"He's undergoing several important tests today," said Jackson spokesman Bob 
Jones. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't think it was a heart attack. He just experienced some discomfort. He 
had been feeling bad the past two or three days." 
</P>
<P>
Jackson, 31, was rehearsing dance steps, which he uses as a form of exercise, 
at his Encino home when he began experiencing the chest pains Sunday night, 
Jones, said. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson was taken to the emergency room at St. John's Hospital and Health 
Center in Santa Monica about 9 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson was staying in the same hospital as his friend Elizabeth Taylor, who 
has been recovering from a near-fatal bout of pneumonia and complications for 
nearly two months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
