<P>
BUCKEY DEFENSE ASKS ACQUITTALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defense attorneys for Ray Buckey, the sole defendant remaining in the McMartin 
Pre-School molestation case, asked the judge today to acquit Buckey of five of 
the eight charges on which he is being retried. 
</P>
<P>
In a written motion, Danny Davis, the chief defense attorney, argued that 
prosecutors, who rested their case Friday, failed to present evidence in 
support of the charges. 
</P>
<P>
The motion will be argued Tuesday, after which time Superior Court Judge 
Stanley Weisberg will render his decision. Buckey, 32, is scheduled to testify 
that day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
