<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
DEA SMASHES MAFIA DRUG RING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Federal agents today smashed a Mafia drug ring they said committed as many as 
seven murders and arrested about 25 people, including a reputed mobster known 
as "Tommy Karate" with "a reputation for chopping people up." 
</P>
<P>
Drug Enforcement Administration agents arrested Thomas (Tommy Karate) Pitera, a 
reputed member of the Bonanno crime family who they charged headed the ring, 
and more than 25 others named in the cocaine and heroin conspiracy indictment. 
</P>
<P>
Law enforcement officials said Pitera has killed as many as 30 people, 
including a Gambino crime family associate who was believed to be an FBI 
informant and was slain as a favor to reputed Gambino crime family boss John 
Gotti. 
</P>
</TEXT>
