<P>
The racketeering trial of former Philippines First Lady Imelda Marcos, who was 
hospitalized after collapsing in court last week, was rescheduled today to 
resume June 12. 
</P>
<P>
Marcos was released from New York Hospital-Cornell Medical Center on Sunday 
after being treated for a stomach ailment. She was taken to the hospital 
Thursday after coughing up blood and collapsing in the courtroom. 
</P>
