<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S A SWEEP: FIRST 4 HORSES SHARE TRAINER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RUIDOSO DOWNS, N.M. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trainer Jack Brooks scored a rare sweep of the top four places in Sunday's 
$246,600 Kansas Derby for quarter horses as his 3-year-old colt Special Project 
led the way. 
</P>
<P>
Following Special Project across the finish line of the 400-yard sprint were 
Sweet N Special, Rockin Alene and Strawberry Silk, who last September gave 
Brooks an unprecedented fifth victory in the All American Futurity, the world's 
richest quarter-horse race. 
</P>
<P>
Special Project covered the distance in a Kansas Derby record time of 19.43. 
</P>
<P>
The four horses were all trained by Brooks, who over the last decade has 
established himself as the top quarter-horse trainer in the country. 
</P>
<P>
Special Project earned $101,329.54 for owners Lindsey Burbank and John Douglas 
of Leesburg, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The total payoff for the four Brooks-trained horses was $183,840.54. 
</P>
</TEXT>
